<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1014.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-24">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 24, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Chinese Government has asked the Baldwin Locomotive Works for a
                                loan of £300,000 for five or eight years on condition that during
                                that period China purchase locomotives to the same amount. The
                                Baldwin agent here wishes to know the attitude of the American
                                Government. I call attention to the negotiations proceeding with
                                various commercial houses, probably without the consent of their
                                Governments, which seem likely to secure for Europe for some years
                                to come Chinese markets in which the United States is
                                interested.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Calhoun.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>